Package InfrastructureManager.ModuleManagement

Class Runner

java.lang.Object
InfrastructureManager.PlatformObject
InfrastructureManager.ModuleManagement.Runner
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Runnable
Direct Known Subclasses:
RestServerRunner
public class Runner
extends PlatformObject
implements java.lang.Runnable
Class implementing the Runnable interface to be run in different threads. The operation it performs when running is configurable and normally done by a PlatformModule Each runner is related to an input and in most cases, performs the operation of reading from input, mapping and sending to output.

  • Constructor Details

    • Runner

      public Runner​(ImmutablePlatformModule ownerModule, java.lang.String name, PlatformInput input)
      Creates a new Runner based on its ownerModule, a name and the input it is bounded to.
      Parameters:
      ownerModule - Owner module of this runner. This will normally trigger its execution
      name - Name for this runner
      input - Input to bound to this runner. One runner can only be related to one input.

    • run

      public void run()
      Overriding of the run method in the Runnable interface Checks for exit and pause flags and runs the operation defined in setRunOperation(RunnerOperation) in a loop. The loop only finished when exit() is called on the runner
